{
  "text": "Later studies of the same mouse line found subtle but progressive motor impairment in mice after 12 months of age [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Stefanova and colleagues [CITATION_3] observed neuronal loss in the substantia nigra pars compacta (SNc) and locus coeruleus in PLP-h\u03b1-syn mice correlating with a subtle motor phenotype of reduced hind limb stride length. A more recent study [CITATION_4] reported widespread \u03b1-synuclein pathology with distribution analysis revealing the highest burden in the globus pallidus. There was also a 31.4 % reduction in dopaminergic neurons in the SNc compared to non-transgenic mice. The motor phenotype was again subtle with progressive impairment in only one out of three tests.",
